Cell.Text: Glad to see you finally came to to your senses. Ready to make some quick coin?
Running a little light in the pockets, are we lad?
Running a little light in the pockets, are we lass?
Your pockets... they're a little low on coin. I can tell.
It all comes from sizing someone up at first glance. The way they walk, they way they carry themselves. It's a dead giveaway.

Node.Caption: TG00BrynjolfIntroBranch02: How could you possibly know that?

Cell.Text: Oh, but that's where you're wrong, lad. Wealth is my business. And if you play your cards right, a part of yours too.
Oh, but that's where you're wrong, lass. Wealth is my business. And if you play your cards right, a part of yours too.

Node.Caption: TG00BrynjolfIntroBranch03: My wealth is none of your business.

Cell.Text: I've cooked up a little scheme here in the Grand Plaza. You help me out with it, and I'll cut you in for some of the loot.

Node.Caption: TG00BrynjolfIntroBranch04: What do you have in mind?

Cell.Text: Simple; I'm going to cause a distraction and you're going to take one of those orachalcum rings off of Grelka's stall over there. | Once you have it, I want you to place it in Brandish Begin-Again's pocket who'll be occupied and should make an easy target.

Node.Caption: TG00BrynjolfIntroBranch06: Sounds good. What do I have to do?

Cell.Text: Sorry... I usually have a nose for this kind of thing. I could have sworn you possessed... | Never mind then. Perhaps I misjudged. If you change your mind, I'll be here.
